explanation: The solution leverages the property that the achievable water amounts form a set of multiples of the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the jug capacities. It first checks if the sum of the jug capacities is less than the target, returning false if so. Then, it determines if the target is achievable by checking if it's a multiple of the GCD of x and y. The GCD is calculated efficiently using the Euclidean algorithm.

